WEBVTT

00:02.102 --> 00:04.970
He rally
in tennessee went over great.

00:05.006 --> 00:06.655
People are loving that
you're addressing the feud

00:06.774 --> 00:07.973
with dr. Julien head on.

00:08.059 --> 00:09.124
- Good.
I'm glad to hear it.

00:09.243 --> 00:10.642
- The polls are still showing
a tight race, though.

00:10.745 --> 00:11.810
It's gonna go down to the wire.

00:11.896 --> 00:13.145
- We're making one final push

00:13.247 --> 00:14.730
through the rust belt,
several stops a day,

00:14.848 --> 00:16.015
right up until November 4th.

00:16.100 --> 00:18.000
- I love it.
And I'm up for all of it.

00:18.119 --> 00:19.385
I'll see you guys
in eight hours.

00:19.487 --> 00:20.419
- What?

00:20.521 --> 00:21.653
Where are you going?

00:21.756 --> 00:22.988
- I'm going to meet
an old friend for lunch.

00:23.074 --> 00:24.757
- But it's two days
before the election.

00:24.859 --> 00:25.924
- I know.
It's exciting, right?

00:26.027 --> 00:27.726
We're almost
at the finish line.

00:27.862 --> 00:29.128
- Can't you reschedule?

00:29.230 --> 00:30.612
- No, you don't want that.
Trust me,

00:30.731 --> 00:32.931
nothing but good will come
out of this lunch.

00:33.034 --> 00:35.067
Randall, let's roll.
- Really?

00:35.202 --> 00:36.719
- Yeah.
- Okay.

00:36.837 --> 00:38.871
I'll bring you back
my leftover lasagna.

00:38.956 --> 00:39.988
Come on, guys.

00:40.107 --> 00:42.708
- What if it's not
an italian restaurant, randall?

00:44.311 --> 00:47.413
- So... Who is this friend?

00:47.498 --> 00:49.281
- Oh, somebody
who's very important to me.

00:49.383 --> 00:50.616
We made a promise
to each other

00:50.718 --> 00:51.984
a long time ago that,

00:52.086 --> 00:53.819
no matter what we had
going on in our lives,

00:53.921 --> 00:55.788
we're going
to meet up this same time,

00:55.890 --> 00:57.423
every single year,
and we're going to have lunch,

00:57.508 --> 00:59.691
and we were just going
to check in with each other.

01:00.428 --> 01:02.795
Just had so much
on my mind lately.

01:02.897 --> 01:05.881
- So do you want to, like,
pre-chat about the things

01:05.999 --> 01:08.817
you're going to chat about
to see if maybe I can fix it?

01:08.936 --> 01:10.252
- No, I don't think so.

01:11.038 --> 01:12.438
- Oh, okay.

01:13.173 --> 01:14.339
- Hey, come on.

01:14.475 --> 01:16.658
You and I chat all the time.
- Yeah, no, yeah.

01:16.777 --> 01:18.627
- We have lot of chances
to chat, me and you.

01:18.745 --> 01:20.279
We've been chatting for weeks.
- Of course. Yeah.

01:20.364 --> 01:21.947
You're right.
- Hey, look, man, I'm sorry.

01:22.049 --> 01:23.499
But when I make
somebody a promise,

01:23.617 --> 01:24.483
I do my best to keep it.

01:25.519 --> 01:27.086
It's part of my code,
and I try to live by it.

01:27.221 --> 01:28.654
It's a lesson I learned
from my dad.

01:28.739 --> 01:31.090
<i> Back in nashville,</i>
<i> after a rough patch,</i>

01:31.192 --> 01:33.158
<i> we were all</i>
<i> under the same roof again.</i>

01:33.260 --> 01:34.960
<i> Traveling the circuit</i>
<i> with my dad,</i>

01:35.062 --> 01:37.729
<i> I saw the grind</i>
<i> he put himself through.</i>

01:37.865 --> 01:40.265
<i>And let me tell you, it puts</i>
<i> a presidential campaign</i>

01:40.367 --> 01:41.316
<i> to shame.</i>

01:42.536 --> 01:44.036
<i> The older he got,</i>
<i> the more everything hurt.</i>

01:44.171 --> 01:45.370
<i> And the older I got,</i>

01:45.472 --> 01:47.172
<i> the less</i>
<i> he could hide it from me.</i>

01:47.308 --> 01:49.174
<i> I knew my dad was</i>
<i> struggling to rebuild</i>

01:49.276 --> 01:52.294
<i> his relationships</i>
<i> and his career,</i>

01:52.413 --> 01:55.264
<i> but now I saw he was</i>
<i> also struggling physically.</i>

01:55.382 --> 01:57.182
♪

01:57.284 --> 02:00.085
<i> when I was a kid,</i>
<i>I wanted to be just like him.</i>

02:00.171 --> 02:01.987
<i>I thought he was a superhero.</i>
[crowd cheers]

02:02.072 --> 02:03.972
<i> but as I grew up,</i>
<i> I realized</i>

02:04.091 --> 02:06.592
<i> my old man was human,</i>
<i> just like the rest of us.</i>

02:06.694 --> 02:10.195
<i> [huey lewis & the news'</i>
<i>"workin' for a livin'" plays]</i>

02:10.281 --> 02:11.964
<i> it was hard</i>
<i> seeing him like that.</i>

02:12.099 --> 02:14.233
<i> - ♪ what they giving 'cause</i>
<i> I'm working for a livin' ♪</i>

02:14.335 --> 02:17.336
<i> - so I did what</i>
<i>a broke kid could do to help.</i>

02:17.438 --> 02:18.737
<i> - ♪ whoa </i>

02:18.823 --> 02:20.956
<i> ♪ taking what you're giving </i>

02:23.310 --> 02:25.043
- we're still
a little short this month.

02:26.497 --> 02:27.980
- I'm a little short
on ice in this drink.

02:28.065 --> 02:29.248
[laughs]

02:29.350 --> 02:31.216
hey, dewey,
go grab me a few cubes.

02:31.318 --> 02:32.818
- Rocky, I'm serious.

02:32.920 --> 02:34.853
My temp job doesn't pay
till next month.

02:34.955 --> 02:35.654
- There's no sweat.

02:36.490 --> 02:37.840
I got the lawler match
on Saturday.

02:37.958 --> 02:39.892
And I'll ask for a few
extra shows just to be safe.

02:40.027 --> 02:41.293
- But you can barely walk.

02:41.395 --> 02:43.562
What if you skip Saturday
and we take it easy,

02:43.697 --> 02:45.664
you know, go get
some pancakes or something?

02:45.799 --> 02:47.699
- Well 'cause,
if I don't show up,

02:47.801 --> 02:49.935
jerry doesn't pay me,
and we can't make rent.

02:49.970 --> 02:51.153
- I don't understand
why you don't get paid

02:51.271 --> 02:52.771
more than these other guys.

02:52.857 --> 02:54.373
You were a wwf champ.

02:54.475 --> 02:56.642
- I'm working my way
back up the ladder, son.

02:56.777 --> 02:58.210
It'll all work itself out.

03:00.314 --> 03:01.547
- We're out of ice.

03:06.187 --> 03:08.020
- See?
Worked itself out.

03:11.575 --> 03:12.941
- Hey, rock.

03:13.060 --> 03:13.926
A new promoter
was asking about you.

03:14.061 --> 03:15.410
- Really?
Who?

03:15.529 --> 03:16.728
- This guy, jarvis.

03:16.814 --> 03:17.829
He's new,
but he's got a lot of money

03:17.932 --> 03:19.231
for some big-time shows.

03:19.333 --> 03:20.532
Said he wants you to headline.

03:20.618 --> 03:22.167
I can put you in touch
if you're interested.

03:22.269 --> 03:24.002
- Oh, thank you,
jerry.

03:24.104 --> 03:25.304
I was about due
for some good news.

03:25.439 --> 03:27.372
- Yeah, you deserve it, champ.
- [chuckles]

03:27.458 --> 03:29.041
- ho ho!
Okay, gentlemen,

03:29.143 --> 03:30.959
it is time for me to announce
some good news.

03:31.078 --> 03:32.744
- Jerry, you ain't gotta
tell everybody.

03:32.846 --> 03:34.930
- I just heard
from vince mcmahon

03:35.049 --> 03:36.732
that this big boy right here

03:36.850 --> 03:38.467
is getting called up
to the wwf!

03:38.585 --> 03:39.785
[all cheer and applaud]

03:39.870 --> 03:41.853
- congrats, champ.
- Way to go, crusher.

03:41.939 --> 03:43.789
- Thank you.
Thanks, boys.

03:43.924 --> 03:45.407
But hey,
it's not crusher anymore.

03:45.526 --> 03:47.392
From now on,

03:47.494 --> 03:52.364
it's bam bam bigelow.
<i> - Bam bam!</i>

03:52.449 --> 03:54.066
- [chuckling] okay.
- That's nice.

03:54.168 --> 03:54.967
- You got it, bam bam.

03:55.970 --> 03:57.069
Now since this is
his last match with us,

03:57.204 --> 03:58.270
he's gonna headline,

03:58.355 --> 04:00.822
and he's made a special request
to face the soulman.

04:00.941 --> 04:01.823
You good, rock?

04:01.942 --> 04:03.058
- You know it.
[all cheer]

04:04.411 --> 04:05.527
<i> - it must have been hard</i>
<i>for your dad to see young guys</i>

04:05.646 --> 04:08.580
like bam bam rise to the top
while he stayed behind.

04:08.666 --> 04:10.933
- No, my dad was always
very happy

04:11.051 --> 04:11.850
to see somebody make it.

04:12.786 --> 04:13.485
As a matter of fact,
he did all he could

04:13.587 --> 04:14.736
to help get the guys over.

04:14.855 --> 04:16.788
- Another part of his code?
- Absolutely.

04:16.890 --> 04:18.290
- We've got
a very special guest today,

04:18.392 --> 04:20.759
the superstar,
randy "macho man" savage.

04:20.861 --> 04:23.195
[audience cheers]

04:23.297 --> 04:24.863
- it's great to be here, king.

04:24.965 --> 04:26.615
- Tell everybody
what brings you to memphis.

04:26.734 --> 04:28.367
- Well, as you know,
jerry lawler,

04:28.469 --> 04:30.969
this is where it all began
for the macho man,

04:31.071 --> 04:32.571
and I love coming home!

04:32.673 --> 04:34.172
Ooh yeah!

04:34.275 --> 04:35.507
[audience cheers]
- they love it.

04:35.609 --> 04:39.077
- And tomorrow, I have
the privilege of opening

04:39.179 --> 04:41.413
a brand-new sears location

04:41.515 --> 04:43.415
right here in downtown memphis.

04:43.517 --> 04:45.050
Stop by
and say hello.

04:45.152 --> 04:46.985
That goes for you too,
jerry lawler.

04:47.087 --> 04:49.354
- I'm more
of a woolworth's man.

04:49.456 --> 04:50.756
- You're insane!

04:50.858 --> 04:53.025
- Now entering the ring,

04:53.127 --> 04:55.027
being accompanied
by his manager,

04:55.129 --> 04:57.029
downtown bruno,

04:57.131 --> 04:58.930
weighing 390 pounds,

04:59.033 --> 05:02.501
he is bam bam bigelow!

05:02.603 --> 05:03.986
[crowd booing]

05:04.104 --> 05:08.206
and his opponent,
former wwf tag team champion,

05:08.309 --> 05:10.442
weighing 243 pounds,

05:10.544 --> 05:14.079
soulman rocky johnson!

05:14.181 --> 05:16.898
- Ooh, yeah!
The soulman.

05:17.017 --> 05:19.885
- That there is a contract
to wrestle in the wwf.

05:19.987 --> 05:22.387
The only way to win is
to sign on that dotted line.

05:22.489 --> 05:24.423
- It's mine.
[bell dings]

05:24.525 --> 05:26.358
- they're circling each other.

05:26.460 --> 05:28.393
Who's going to strike first?

05:28.495 --> 05:30.295
<i> - Now, my dad knew</i>

05:30.397 --> 05:33.465
<i> he wasn't going to win</i>
<i> that contract,</i>

05:33.567 --> 05:35.834
<i>but that didn't mean he wasn't</i>
<i> gonna put on a show.</i>

05:35.936 --> 05:37.803
- Oh, rocky gets him
on the floor!

05:37.888 --> 05:39.504
He gets him on the floor!
[crowd roars]

05:40.307 --> 05:42.174
oh, the turnaround!

05:42.276 --> 05:43.742
- He's on his feet!
Oh!

05:43.877 --> 05:46.511
- And rocky's got the big fella
in a sleeper hold, macho!

05:46.613 --> 05:48.113
- Bam bam better get
to the rope, or it could be

05:48.198 --> 05:49.581
lights out,
yeah!

05:49.683 --> 05:51.783
- Come on.
- So close.

05:51.885 --> 05:53.285
Bruno: Come on!
[taps on ring]

05:53.387 --> 05:54.519
[body thuds]
- he's out!

05:54.621 --> 05:56.088
He's out cold!
[crowd cheers]

05:56.190 --> 05:58.390
- and the soulman
has the contract!

05:58.492 --> 06:01.193
And rocky has won
a coveted spot in the wwf!

06:01.295 --> 06:02.694
He did it!

06:02.796 --> 06:04.863
Hold on, macho.
Look at that contract.

06:04.998 --> 06:06.231
It's signed in red ink.

06:06.316 --> 06:07.566
That's not a binding color
for a contract.

06:07.668 --> 06:09.167
- Ooh, it's gotta be black
or blue.

06:09.269 --> 06:10.936
Everybody knows that, yeah!

06:11.021 --> 06:12.804
- Somebody
must've switched the pen!

06:12.906 --> 06:14.106
It's downtown bruno!

06:14.208 --> 06:15.407
He's got the official pen!
[crowd booing]

06:15.509 --> 06:16.675
- bam bam's back
on his feet.

06:16.777 --> 06:17.776
This match ain't over!

06:17.878 --> 06:19.578
Jerry: Rocky has no idea.

06:22.216 --> 06:24.383
Bruno's distracting the ref!

06:24.485 --> 06:25.550
[crowd groans]

06:25.652 --> 06:26.935
- ref, do your job!

06:27.054 --> 06:28.353
- He didn't see it!
He didn't see it!

06:28.455 --> 06:31.022
The big man's
going to the top rope.

06:31.108 --> 06:32.457
<i> [dramatic chord]</i>

06:37.598 --> 06:39.197
- whoa, a flying headbutt!

06:39.299 --> 06:40.465
Ooh yeah!

06:40.567 --> 06:41.500
- Here we go,
here we go, here we go.

06:41.602 --> 06:43.368
Sign it, sign it.

06:43.470 --> 06:44.336
Sign it, baby!

06:45.339 --> 06:46.338
- And bam bam bigelow
is headed to the wwf!

06:46.440 --> 06:49.374
<i> - That contract</i>
<i> was a gimmick,</i>

06:49.510 --> 06:51.676
<i> but that pain</i>
<i> on my dad's face was real.</i>

06:53.346 --> 06:53.378
.

06:53.546 --> 06:54.746
- Nice work today,
brother.

06:55.849 --> 06:55.881
You made bam bam look

06:56.450 --> 06:56.998
like a million bucks.

06:58.001 --> 06:58.784
- You know, it's easy to act
like I'm in pain

06:59.703 --> 07:01.036
when I'm in tons of pain.
[both laugh]

07:01.154 --> 07:02.954
- randy and I loved
our time in hawaii

07:03.090 --> 07:04.389
when you were running
the circuit there.

07:04.491 --> 07:06.208
The things you were doing,
all the storylines--

07:06.326 --> 07:08.093
it was so innovative.

07:08.195 --> 07:10.762
- Thank you, elizabeth.
Too bad it couldn't last.

07:10.848 --> 07:12.013
- Oh, shoot.

07:12.132 --> 07:13.165
I'm sorry if that's
a sore subject.

07:13.267 --> 07:14.549
- No, no, no, no.
It's fine.

07:14.668 --> 07:16.301
- I never mean
to bring up wrestling,

07:16.386 --> 07:19.404
but it always seems to worm
its way into a conversation.

07:19.506 --> 07:20.639
- Well, honestly, what chance
do we have

07:20.774 --> 07:22.057
being around these two?

07:22.175 --> 07:24.142
- He landed on my damn knee.
[knee clicking]

07:24.278 --> 07:26.545
- I mean, that's bad,
but check this out.

07:26.647 --> 07:27.646
[table thuds]

07:29.032 --> 07:31.032
- shopping for gloves
must be hard.

07:31.151 --> 07:32.284
- I'll miss a couple
of matches,

07:32.386 --> 07:34.069
but vince said
he'll take care of me.

07:34.188 --> 07:36.488
- The wwf pays you
even when you don't wrestle?

07:36.623 --> 07:38.490
- Yeah, you betcha.

07:38.575 --> 07:40.659
- Hey, uh, you're paying
for this next round too, right?

07:40.794 --> 07:44.246
- Actually,
next round is on sears.

07:44.364 --> 07:45.580
You know, I get
that big store opening

07:45.699 --> 07:48.333
tomorrow, so I can't go
too crazy tonight.

07:48.919 --> 07:50.669
- I got you.
- I'm good, son.

07:50.754 --> 07:52.170
Hey, you wanna be useful,

07:52.306 --> 07:53.505
come help me
carry these drinks.

07:54.641 --> 07:57.476
- So, ata,
how are you guys doing?

07:57.561 --> 07:58.510
Huh?

07:59.596 --> 08:00.178
I didn't want to ask rocky,
'cause you know him.

08:01.098 --> 08:02.514
He'll always spin it.
- We're all right.

08:02.649 --> 08:04.349
Somehow, the bills
always get paid.

08:04.485 --> 08:05.734
[chuckles]

08:05.853 --> 08:08.854
rocky's working nonstop,
but he never complains.

08:08.989 --> 08:11.022
- Hey, if you didn't
order fernet,

08:11.158 --> 08:12.023
I got you one anyway.

08:12.159 --> 08:13.859
All: [chuckle]

08:13.994 --> 08:15.076
- hey...

08:15.195 --> 08:16.111
To sears.

08:16.230 --> 08:17.412
- [chuckling] oh, sears.

08:17.531 --> 08:19.114
Best place on earth.
[glasses clink]

08:19.232 --> 08:20.665
- that was so much fun!

08:20.767 --> 08:22.133
- We have to do it again.

08:22.236 --> 08:24.169
- [chuckles] yes,
and just us next time.

08:24.271 --> 08:26.204
- Oh, perfect.
I need a night off

08:26.306 --> 08:27.906
from thinking about wrestlers
and wrestling.

08:28.008 --> 08:29.307
- We'll leave all that at home.

08:29.409 --> 08:30.809
We'll be like
500 pounds lighter.

08:30.911 --> 08:32.244
[both laugh]

08:32.346 --> 08:34.412
- and after that,
I never watched another thing

08:34.515 --> 08:36.081
bea arthur did.
[laughs]

08:36.183 --> 08:37.048
- it makes sense.
Makes sense.

08:38.085 --> 08:39.768
Hey, can I ask you a question?
- Anything, kid.

08:39.887 --> 08:41.136
- Could you talk to my dad,

08:41.254 --> 08:42.888
try and convince him
to apologize to vince

08:43.023 --> 08:45.290
so he can get back
in the wwf?

08:45.392 --> 08:46.441
I bet he'll listen to you.

08:46.560 --> 08:47.893
- He'll never do it,
little brother.

08:48.028 --> 08:50.529
You know your dad and his code.

08:50.614 --> 08:52.447
Honestly,
even if he did apologize,

08:52.566 --> 08:53.782
I don't think it would matter.

08:53.901 --> 08:55.283
That chapter is closed.

08:55.402 --> 08:57.168
- He's given everything
to wrestling,

08:57.271 --> 08:59.321
and now that he's getting
older, that's it?

08:59.439 --> 09:01.706
- I get it.
It's a tough business.

09:01.808 --> 09:04.543
You want stability,
you work at state farm.

09:05.245 --> 09:07.212
Look, have a little faith
in your old man.

09:07.297 --> 09:10.131
He's a fighter.
He'll always end up on a--

09:10.250 --> 09:11.216
[sign rattles]

09:11.301 --> 09:12.717
[chuckles]

09:12.803 --> 09:15.954
that is what happens when
you wear sunglasses at night.

09:16.056 --> 09:18.256
Ooh yeah!

09:18.392 --> 09:20.342
<i> - Talking to macho man</i>
<i> had me questioning</i>

09:20.460 --> 09:22.093
<i> the cost of my dad's code.</i>

09:22.229 --> 09:23.395
Jeff jarrett knows
that's his bad shoulder.

09:23.480 --> 09:24.813
- It's like mama said.

09:24.932 --> 09:26.731
Sometimes it "bes" that way.

09:28.001 --> 09:29.568
[arm thuds]
- man,

09:29.653 --> 09:31.236
my dad brings it
every night,

09:31.321 --> 09:32.704
and he has
nothing to show for it.

09:32.806 --> 09:34.239
- [groaning]

09:34.324 --> 09:35.440
- I'm going to be
the one to make sure my dad

09:35.525 --> 09:37.275
doesn't retire broke
and crippled.

09:40.447 --> 09:42.581
- I bet your daddy
don't regret a second.

09:42.666 --> 09:43.832
And neither do I,

09:43.951 --> 09:45.116
because the wrestling business

09:45.202 --> 09:46.835
is the greatest in the world,
dewey.

09:47.421 --> 09:49.204
Do you know that I could walk
into a restaurant,

09:49.322 --> 09:52.123
and that entire place
will start booing me?

09:52.209 --> 09:53.291
Last week, I had a little kid,

09:53.427 --> 09:54.542
maybe nine years old,
came up to me,

09:54.661 --> 09:57.379
and he hated me so much,
he spit in my face.

09:57.497 --> 09:58.880
You know how beautiful that is?

09:58.999 --> 10:00.515
To move somebody in that way?

10:00.634 --> 10:01.800
And that,

10:01.885 --> 10:03.184
that is wrestling.

10:03.303 --> 10:04.936
[rock music playing]

10:05.022 --> 10:06.471
- [groans]

10:07.357 --> 10:09.107
