Hey, check it out.

14:18.825 --> 14:20.508
This must be what
sylvester stallone feels like

14:20.627 --> 14:21.860
all the time.

14:21.962 --> 14:23.361
- [laughs]

14:23.446 --> 14:25.063
- [chuckles]
there's my headliner.

14:25.165 --> 14:27.465
It's going to be big tonight.
- Hey, mr. Jarvis.

14:27.567 --> 14:28.967
Yeah, I saw that marquee.

14:29.102 --> 14:30.001
- Hey, hold out your hand.

14:30.103 --> 14:31.769
- Uh-oh.

14:31.872 --> 14:33.805
- Bam! I have the money
up front, right?

14:33.890 --> 14:35.106
Deal's a deal.

14:35.208 --> 14:36.808
Come on, let me show you
the green room.

14:38.278 --> 14:40.578
This is
your private dressing room.

14:41.615 --> 14:42.714
- Private?

14:42.816 --> 14:43.781
Nice.

14:43.867 --> 14:45.083
- Got its own bathroom, too.

14:45.185 --> 14:47.118
- A man needs
solitude on the throne.

14:47.220 --> 14:48.853
Rip, elvis presley.
- [chuckles]

14:48.955 --> 14:51.089
we're just gonna cut
a little promo first,

14:51.174 --> 14:52.707
if that's all right?
- Yeah, sure, of course.

14:52.826 --> 14:54.108
- Hey, craig!

14:54.227 --> 14:55.193
I like giving
the audience the feeling

14:55.295 --> 14:56.895
they're getting a sneak peek
behind the scenes.

14:56.997 --> 14:58.313
- I like that.

14:58.431 --> 14:59.998
My wife was working
on a similar idea

15:00.133 --> 15:01.432
out in hawaii
a few years ago.

15:01.534 --> 15:03.184
- So, yeah,
here's what I'm thinking.

15:03.303 --> 15:05.987
You'll be over there...

15:06.106 --> 15:07.188
Eating your chicken
and your watermelon,

15:07.307 --> 15:08.756
and you're pumped
for the match.

15:08.875 --> 15:11.109
You're feeling cocky,
like, you know, talking street

15:11.194 --> 15:13.144
to your opponent--
- hey, stop. Stop.

15:13.246 --> 15:14.329
No.

15:14.447 --> 15:15.780
I won't do
that racist garbage.

15:15.882 --> 15:16.881
- Racist?

15:16.967 --> 15:18.283
This isn't racist.

15:18.418 --> 15:20.385
Other guys got
no problem with it.

15:20.520 --> 15:22.520
<i>- That wasn't the first time</i>
<i> that my dad had been asked</i>

15:22.622 --> 15:24.455
to work a gimmick
like that.

15:24.557 --> 15:27.859
And that kind of overt racism

15:27.944 --> 15:29.627
may seem shocking these days,

15:29.729 --> 15:31.663
but there were certain parts
of pro wrestling

15:31.748 --> 15:34.699
back then, in the early '80s,
where that wasn't uncommon.

15:34.801 --> 15:36.034
- Mm, I believe it.

15:36.119 --> 15:38.503
- I was always really proud
of my dad,

15:38.638 --> 15:41.005
because regardless of how badly
he needed that money,

15:41.107 --> 15:42.674
and we needed
that money, man...

15:42.809 --> 15:44.125
He just wouldn't do it.

15:45.345 --> 15:46.778
He'd call that
part of his code.

15:46.880 --> 15:49.364
- Hey, man, I don't care
what other guys do.

15:49.482 --> 15:51.215
Not me.

15:51.351 --> 15:52.533
- It's part of the deal, rocky.

15:52.652 --> 15:54.185
- Not gonna happen.
Come on, dwayne.

15:54.321 --> 15:55.586
[upbeat music]

15:55.722 --> 15:58.556
oh, I'm keeping this.

15:58.658 --> 15:59.924
Racist tax.

16:03.629 --> 16:05.363
- I don't know
how you stayed so calm.

16:05.382 --> 16:06.381
We should have beat his ass.

16:06.416 --> 16:09.434
- Son, there's gonna
always be folks like that.

16:09.469 --> 16:11.002
Always.

16:11.037 --> 16:13.254
And they're gonna ask you to do
things you don't wanna do,

16:13.306 --> 16:15.606
no matter how big
you think you are,

16:15.642 --> 16:17.541
or what line of work you're in.

16:17.560 --> 16:19.594
It's gonna happen.

16:19.646 --> 16:21.346
Just promise me one thing.

16:22.182 --> 16:25.716
Don't let anyone change
who you are.

16:25.735 --> 16:27.735
You hear me?

16:27.771 --> 16:29.887
You make your own code,
and don't let anyone

16:29.906 --> 16:31.889
force you to break it.

16:31.908 --> 16:33.741
Deal?
- Deal.

16:37.614 --> 16:40.164
Well, I guess we got
a free night now.

16:41.868 --> 16:44.702
Mmm.
- Oh, these are delicious.

16:44.738 --> 16:46.454
- Fluffy as hell.
- [chuckles lightly]

16:46.506 --> 16:48.406
- how about we hit
the gym early tomorrow?

16:48.425 --> 16:50.574
Put these carbs to work.
- Well, if we're doing that,

16:50.593 --> 16:51.742
I'm getting some whipped cream.

16:51.761 --> 16:53.294
- Get it, dad.
- I'm getting it, son.

16:53.346 --> 16:55.013
[both chuckle]

16:55.048 --> 16:57.098
[trimmer whirs]
- ooh yeah!

16:57.133 --> 16:58.916
[chuckles]
- I'll take it.

16:58.952 --> 17:00.485
- Oh, good choice.
Lane three's wide open.

17:00.520 --> 17:01.786
Michelle will help you, yeah.

17:01.821 --> 17:02.987
[chuckles]

17:03.023 --> 17:05.023
- hey, randy.
- Boss man.

17:05.058 --> 17:06.290
- I didn't expect
to see you back tonight.

17:06.326 --> 17:07.925
- Oh, you know,
I thought I would come

17:07.961 --> 17:10.461
and soak up some
of that new store energy.

17:10.497 --> 17:12.480
[inhales deeply]
ooh yeah.

17:12.532 --> 17:14.198
- I wanna be clear,

17:14.234 --> 17:16.334
I can't pay you for the time
you've spent helping customers.

17:16.369 --> 17:18.836
- This is not work
for the macho man.

17:18.872 --> 17:22.323
No, this is
an absolute pleasure, yeah.

17:22.375 --> 17:24.742
- To be honest,
it's against company policy

17:24.777 --> 17:25.910
to act as an employee

17:25.945 --> 17:27.378
without attending
the trainee program.

17:27.414 --> 17:28.546
- [sighs]

17:28.581 --> 17:30.114
- in lieu of payment,

17:30.150 --> 17:31.682
why don't you take one
of these party cans

17:31.718 --> 17:33.117
of slim jims?

17:33.153 --> 17:34.635
Token of our appreciation.

17:34.671 --> 17:35.970
- Mm-hmm.

17:36.005 --> 17:37.522
Smoked beef snack.

17:37.557 --> 17:39.157
Spicy.

17:39.192 --> 17:41.392
You know, I never did have
a slim jim before, but hey,

17:41.428 --> 17:44.695
if they sell them at sears,
I know I'm gonna love 'em.

17:44.731 --> 17:46.397
Ooh yeah.

17:46.433 --> 17:47.732
[chuckles]

17:47.767 --> 17:49.901
get in here. Yeah.
