- Mm.
You know, I have to admit,

19:12.936 --> 19:14.852
I had doubts
about your father's code,

19:14.887 --> 19:16.571
but now I am
fully on board.

19:16.606 --> 19:18.222
- Well, I could tell you
a thousand stories

19:18.241 --> 19:19.440
that'll make you change
your mind back again.

19:19.492 --> 19:21.409
[both chuckle]

19:21.444 --> 19:23.611
- all right.
Well, I'm sorry, my friend.

19:23.663 --> 19:24.745
This is where I leave you.

19:24.781 --> 19:26.614
- Wha--
- it's a private lunch.

19:26.666 --> 19:28.616
- Well, I won't say anything.
I'll just sit in the corner.

19:28.668 --> 19:30.751
- No, not this time.
- But I'm your friend, too.

19:30.787 --> 19:31.953
Come on.

19:32.005 --> 19:33.838
Sorry, I--
- you are my friend.

19:33.873 --> 19:35.790
- I am, right?
- I'm gonna eat lunch.

19:35.842 --> 19:37.375
- Okay, let's go.
- No, no, no.

19:37.410 --> 19:39.293
I'm going to eat lunch.
- You know what, I--

19:39.345 --> 19:40.645
- no, no, no.
- No, yeah.

19:40.680 --> 19:43.915
<i> [heavy music]</i>

19:43.950 --> 19:46.133
[plane whines]

19:46.186 --> 19:48.469
<i> - so I was up ten points</i>
<i> in the polls,</i>

19:48.521 --> 19:52.290
and this kid who I went
to school with, julien,

19:52.325 --> 19:54.625
starts spreading
all these lies about me.

19:54.661 --> 19:57.195
And now the whole thing
is a coin toss.

19:57.230 --> 19:59.647
It could go either way.

19:59.699 --> 20:02.650
All this hard work I've put in,
this entire campaign,

20:02.702 --> 20:06.837
and now I'm back to square one.

20:06.873 --> 20:09.073
What do I do, forest?

20:09.108 --> 20:11.242
- Dwayne,
the point of this yearly lunch

20:11.277 --> 20:14.512
is to always be 100% honest
with each other, right?

20:14.547 --> 20:16.664
- Always, yes.

20:16.716 --> 20:18.916
Like I was honest with you
last year, when I told you

20:18.951 --> 20:20.301
I didn't like the smell
of your cologne.

20:20.336 --> 20:22.253
[both chuckle]
- and I changed it.

20:22.288 --> 20:25.306
I listened to you,
and I changed it.

20:25.341 --> 20:26.674
Back to the matter at hand.

20:26.726 --> 20:30.127
I don't think that being back
at square one

20:30.146 --> 20:31.846
is actually
what's bothering you.

20:31.898 --> 20:35.199
It's like
this beautiful barbaresco.

20:35.235 --> 20:38.502
Its grapes are grown
in northern Italy,

20:38.521 --> 20:41.355
alongside its brother,
barolo.

20:41.391 --> 20:42.690
Same region,

20:42.725 --> 20:44.442
different varietal.

20:44.477 --> 20:45.526
- Look, I guess, forest.

20:45.561 --> 20:47.612
I'm a tequila man.
You know that.

20:47.647 --> 20:49.647
- You can't be fully you

20:49.682 --> 20:52.199
if you're dealing
with unfinished business.

20:52.235 --> 20:54.952
You have to address
this julien problem

20:54.988 --> 20:56.370
at the heart of the problem.

20:56.406 --> 20:58.990
<i> ♪ </i>

20:59.025 --> 21:01.876
- what do you mean?
